# Secrets template. There are two gitignored destinations, by purpose:
#
#   .dev.vars  — Worker *bindings* for local dev (the Wrangler/Miniflare
#                convention; read as `c.env.<KEY>`). In production these are
#                set with `wrangler secret put <KEY>`, NOT from any file.
#   .env       — values used by local Node/Bun *scripts* (never by the Worker).
#                Production copies are kept here under a `PROD_` prefix so the
#                name signals "this is the live value, used locally."
#
# Copy the relevant block to the matching file and fill in real values.

# ── .dev.vars (local Worker bindings) ───────────────────────────────────────
# Shared secret for verifying GitHub webhook signatures (X-Hub-Signature-256).
# This is the LOCAL-dev value; production's is set via `wrangler secret put
# GITHUB_WEBHOOK_SECRET` and may differ.
GITHUB_WEBHOOK_SECRET=

# Google OAuth (PROG-34): the in-app sign-in that replaced Cloudflare Access.
# Create an OAuth 2.0 Client (type "Web application") in the Google Cloud
# Console and add the redirect URI <origin>/api/auth/callback (e.g.
# http://localhost:8000/api/auth/callback for dev, and the production URL).
# If GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID / SESSION_SECRET are absent, the Worker runs in the
# unauthenticated local-dev mode (every write attributed to the owner) — so
# these are only needed to exercise the real Google flow locally.
GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID=
GOOGLE_CLIENT_SECRET=
# HS256 key used to sign the session (and OAuth state) cookies. Any long random
# string; rotating it invalidates existing sessions.
SESSION_SECRET=
# Static bearer token for non-interactive clients (MCP server, `progress work`
# CLI, dogfood scripts). Sent as `Authorization: Bearer <token>`; resolves to
# the owner. Any long random string.
PROGRESS_API_TOKEN=
# Comma-separated super-admins (D43). These Google accounts can manage the
# runtime sign-in allowlist on the Admin page and always have access. Everyone
# else must be added to that allowlist (stored in D1) to sign in. The old
# ALLOWED_EMAILS name is still read as a fallback during migration.
SUPER_ADMIN_EMAILS=bryan@mysteryexperience.com
# Optional: force the OAuth redirect origin. Defaults to the request's own
# origin, which is correct for both localhost and production — only set this if
# the Worker sits behind a proxy that rewrites the host.
# APP_BASE_URL=

# ── .env (local scripts; production values, PROD_ prefix) ────────────────────
# Copy of the production webhook secret, kept locally only so it's on hand for
# GitHub-side webhook registration (Settings → Webhooks). Not read by the Worker.
PROD_GITHUB_WEBHOOK_SECRET=

# Copy of the production PROGRESS_API_TOKEN (the value behind `wrangler secret
# put PROGRESS_API_TOKEN`). Read by the MCP server and the dogfood/`progress
# work` scripts to reach the live API non-interactively. The MCP server and CLI
# also accept it under the unprefixed name PROGRESS_API_TOKEN.
PROD_PROGRESS_API_TOKEN=
